# Voice Assistant

Voice Assistant is a Python-based virtual assistant that uses speech recognition and text-to-speech conversion to perform various tasks based on user commands. It can provide information from Wikipedia, open websites, play music, send emails, fetch weather reports, suggest recipes, and more.

## Features

- Speech recognition and text-to-speech conversion
- Greet the user based on the time of day
- Fetch information from Wikipedia
- Open websites such as Google, YouTube, Instagram, etc.
- Play music from a local directory
- Open applications on your laptop
- Send emails to specified recipients
- Provide daily health tips
- Suggest spiritual quotes
- Calculate mathematical expressions
- Fetch weather reports for a given location
- Turn off the voice assistant

## Requirements

- Python 3.x
- pyttsx3 library
- speech_recognition library
- wikipedia library
- webbrowser library
- smtplib library
- pyautogui library
- requests library

Install the required libraries using the following command:

```shell
pip install pyttsx3 speechrecognition wikipedia requests
